  "texts": [
    "Observe that even though IKS only emerges in the presence of explicit Ĉ3z -breaking by strain, q IVC does not directly track the strain and even relatively modest strains produce a substantial q IVC, so it has some features of a true nematic even though it is not one in a strict sense.",
    "And hence also requires that the spin-splitting of the bands in a magnetic field is negligible.",
    "Note that this implicitly assumes that each of the degenerate Fermi surfaces has the same area, or equivalently that the quantum oscillations have a single frequency.",
    "This can be motivated from the discussion of the strong-coupling Chern basis in Section 4.1, where C = στ.",
    "A positive sublattice potential will tend to raise the energy of the σ = A bands relative to the σ = B bands, so the kinetic conduction bands are expected to have C = τ."
